\sqrt{1 - 4x^2}
\frac{16}{16} \cdot \sqrt{1 - 4x^2}
16 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{1 - 4x^2}}{16}
16 \cdot \sqrt{\frac{1 - 4x^2}{4}} \Longleftarrow \text{Took the square root of 16 to get it in the radicand as the divisor}
\sqrt{a\cdot b}=\sqrt{a}\cdot\sqrt{b}
4
\sqrt{1-4x^2}
1-4x^2=4\cdot\frac{1-4x^2}{4}
\sqrt{1-4x^2}=\sqrt{4\cdot\frac{1-4x^2}{4}}=\sqrt{4}\cdot\sqrt{\frac{1-4x^2}{4}}=2\cdot\sqrt{\frac{1-4x^2}{4}}
\dfrac{2}{2} \cdot \sqrt{1-4x^2}
= 2 \cdot \dfrac{\sqrt{1-4x^2}}{2}
= 2 \cdot \dfrac{\sqrt{1-4x^2}}{\sqrt{4}} \qquad \Leftarrow
x = \sqrt{x^2}
= 2 \cdot \sqrt{\dfrac{1-4x^2}{4}} \qquad \Leftarrow
\frac{\sqrt a}{\sqrt b} = \sqrt{\frac a b}
